content:
The RuneScape Wiki also has an article on: rsw:Lunar equipment

Lunar equipment is the ceremonial attire of the Moon Clan, is made by players during the Lunar Diplomacy quest, and may be kept afterwards. All armour and jewellery pieces of the set require 65 Magic and 40 Defence to wear, and the staff requires 65 Magic to wield. After completion of the quest, the pieces of Lunar equipment may be bought from the Oneiromancer on Lunar Isle. Players may not make the items themselves after the quest is complete; they must buy the items if they lose them.

While Lunar armour has lesser magic bonuses compared to other magical armour of a similar level, it is marginally more defensive compared to other magic armours that usually have few to no melee defences. Because of this, it can be considered a crude hybrid between melee armour and magic armour. However, ranged attacks may still cripple the wearer due to the armour's virtually nonexistent ranged defence.

Every part of this set is always lost on death.

This set (except for the Lunar staff) may be stored in a magic wardrobe in the costume room of a player-owned house.
